## `<file-level: imports>`
<!-- checksum: placeholder-symlinks-1 -->

### Purpose
Tests for symbolic links. Targets are stored as `bytes` (per idea.md §6 — Linux semantics: symlink contents are opaque bytes, possibly non-UTF-8).

### Implementation Notes

```python
import pytest

from sqlite_fs.errors import (
    AlreadyExists,
    InvalidXattr,   # not used here but imported elsewhere
    IsADirectory,
    NotFound,
    SymlinkLoop,
)
```

---

## `test_symlink_create_and_readlink(as_root)`
<!-- checksum: placeholder-symlinks-2 -->

### Purpose
Basic round-trip: `symlink` creates, `readlink` returns the same target bytes.

### Postconditions

```python
as_root.symlink(b"/target/path", "/link")
assert as_root.readlink("/link") == b"/target/path"
```

---

## `test_symlink_target_stored_as_bytes(as_root)`
<!-- checksum: placeholder-symlinks-3 -->

### Purpose
Symlink targets are bytes — non-UTF-8 targets round-trip verbatim.

### Postconditions

```python
non_utf8_target = b"\xff\xfe\xfd/path"
as_root.symlink(non_utf8_target, "/link")
assert as_root.readlink("/link") == non_utf8_target
```

---

## `test_symlink_target_need_not_exist(as_root)`
<!-- checksum: placeholder-symlinks-4 -->

### Purpose
Dangling symlinks are allowed — the target is stored opaquely. POSIX matches.

### Postconditions

```python
as_root.symlink(b"/no/such/file", "/dangling")
assert as_root.readlink("/dangling") == b"/no/such/file"
# Stat with follow_symlinks=False works (sees the link itself).
st = as_root.stat("/dangling", follow_symlinks=False)
assert st.kind == "symlink"
# Stat with follow_symlinks=True raises — target doesn't exist.
with pytest.raises(NotFound):
    as_root.stat("/dangling", follow_symlinks=True)
```

---

## `test_stat_follow_symlink(as_root)`
<!-- checksum: placeholder-symlinks-5 -->

### Purpose
`stat` with `follow_symlinks=True` (default) returns the target's stat, not the link's.

### Postconditions

```python
fd = as_root.create("/target", mode=0o644)
as_root.write(fd, b"hello", offset=0)
as_root.close_fd(fd)

as_root.symlink(b"/target", "/link")

st_target = as_root.stat("/target")
st_link_followed = as_root.stat("/link")                            # default follow=True
assert st_link_followed.inode == st_target.inode
assert st_link_followed.size == 5
assert st_link_followed.kind == "file"
```

---

## `test_lstat_does_not_follow(as_root)`
<!-- checksum: placeholder-symlinks-6 -->

### Postconditions

```python
fd = as_root.create("/target"); as_root.close_fd(fd)
as_root.symlink(b"/target", "/link")

st_link = as_root.lstat("/link")
st_target = as_root.stat("/target")

assert st_link.kind == "symlink"
assert st_link.inode != st_target.inode
```

