## `test_readlink_on_non_symlink_raises(as_root)`
<!-- checksum: placeholder-symlinks-8 -->

### Purpose
Calling `readlink` on a regular file or directory raises. We surface this as `IsADirectory` for directories and as a generic `NotFound` misuse for files — actually, POSIX uses EINVAL here. We map to `FilesystemError` subclass `InvalidArgument` (introduced in errors.engspec). For this v1 we raise `NotFound` to keep the error surface small; revisit if it causes interop issues.

### Postconditions

```python
fd = as_root.create("/f"); as_root.close_fd(fd)
with pytest.raises(NotFound):
    as_root.readlink("/f")

as_root.mkdir("/d")
with pytest.raises(NotFound):
    as_root.readlink("/d")
```

---

