## `test_unlink_symlink_removes_only_link(as_root)`
<!-- checksum: placeholder-symlinks-10 -->

### Purpose
`unlink` on a symlink removes the symlink itself, not the target (which may or may not exist).

### Postconditions

```python
fd = as_root.create("/target")
as_root.write(fd, b"data", offset=0)
as_root.close_fd(fd)

as_root.symlink(b"/target", "/link")
as_root.unlink("/link")

# Target still there.
assert as_root.exists("/target")
assert as_root.stat("/target").size == 4

# Link gone.
assert as_root.exists("/link") is False
```

---

## `test_symlink_chain_follow(as_root)`
<!-- checksum: placeholder-symlinks-11 -->

### Purpose
A chain of up to 40 symlinks (MAXSYMLINKS) resolves correctly.

### Postconditions

```python
fd = as_root.create("/target"); as_root.close_fd(fd)
target_inode = as_root.stat("/target").inode

# Build a 10-link chain: /a -> /b -> /c -> ... -> /target
as_root.symlink(b"/target", "/link0")
for i in range(1, 10):
    as_root.symlink(f"/link{i - 1}".encode(), f"/link{i}")

# Following /link9 resolves to /target.
assert as_root.stat("/link9").inode == target_inode
```

---

## `test_symlink_chain_too_long_raises(as_root)`
<!-- checksum: placeholder-symlinks-12 -->

### Purpose
A chain longer than MAXSYMLINKS (40) raises `SymlinkLoop`. This protects against infinite resolution.

### Postconditions

```python
# Build a chain of 42 links ending in a missing target.
as_root.symlink(b"/nonexistent", "/link0")
for i in range(1, 42):
    as_root.symlink(f"/link{i - 1}".encode(), f"/link{i}")

with pytest.raises(SymlinkLoop):
    as_root.stat("/link41", follow_symlinks=True)
```

---

## `test_symlink_loop_raises(as_root)`
<!-- checksum: placeholder-symlinks-13 -->

### Purpose
A direct cycle (`/a -> /a`, or `/a -> /b -> /a`) raises `SymlinkLoop` on follow.

### Postconditions

```python
as_root.symlink(b"/a", "/a")
with pytest.raises(SymlinkLoop):
    as_root.stat("/a", follow_symlinks=True)

# lstat on the cycle works — it doesn't follow.
st = as_root.stat("/a", follow_symlinks=False)
assert st.kind == "symlink"
```

---

## `test_readdir_includes_symlink_kind(as_root)`
<!-- checksum: placeholder-symlinks-14 -->

### Purpose
`readdir` returns `DirEntry(kind="symlink")` for symlink entries, never follows.

### Postconditions

```python
fd = as_root.create("/target"); as_root.close_fd(fd)
as_root.symlink(b"/target", "/link")

entries = {e.name: e.kind for e in as_root.readdir("/")}
assert entries == {"target": "file", "link": "symlink"}
```

